# Persistent Todo Management

**Precedence:** standing user instruction. Overrides any default to minimize todos or add them only when explicitly asked — continuous proactive management is the explicit ask.

- **GitHub issues are the source of truth** for tracked work. The in-session todo tool holds working state.
- **Update the relevant GitHub issue as work progresses** — status, comments, checklists, TDD red-log evidence ([github-issue-workflow.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/github-issue-workflow.mdc)), close when done on the branch where it was implemented.
- **Create a new GitHub issue** whenever work emerges that needs tracking and isn't already covered by an existing issue.
- **Preserve existing items** across topic/task switches — never drop unfinished work.
- **Add items only for real work.** If the answer is "not needed" or "already done", don't add a todo or issue.
- **Treat questions as potential new work**, not interruptions. Capture both the old and new items when the new one genuinely needs doing.
- **Reference todos + issues proactively** to guide the conversation.
